<span id="cb6-3"><a href="#cb6-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">select</span>(race, offpov, age) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb6-4"><a href="#cb6-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">mutate</span>(<span class="at">Race =</span> <span class="fu">factor</span>(<span class="fu">case_when</span>(</span>
<span id="cb6-5"><a href="#cb6-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    race <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="dv">100</span> <span class="sc">~</span> <span class="st">&quot;White&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb6-6"><a href="#cb6-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    race <span class="sc">!=</span> <span class="dv">100</span> <span class="sc">~</span> <span class="st">&quot;Non-White&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb6-7"><a href="#cb6-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  ))) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb6-8"><a href="#cb6-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#filter(age &lt; 80) %&gt;% Since anyone between 80 and 84 is coded as 80, and anyone 85 or above is coded as 85</span></span>
<span id="cb6-9"><a href="#cb6-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">group_by</span>(Race, age) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb6-10"><a href="#cb6-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  srvyr<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">summarize</span>(<span class="at">pov =</span> <span class="fu">survey_mean</span>(offpov)<span class="sc">*</span><span class="dv">100</span>) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb6-11"><a href="#cb6-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">ggplot</span>(<span class="fu">aes</span>(<span class="at">x =</span> age, <span class="at">y =</span> pov, <span class="at">color =</span> Race)) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb6-12"><a href="#cb6-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">geom_line</span>(<span class="at">linewidth =</span> <span class="dv">1</span>) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb6-13"><a href="#cb6-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">scale_x_continuous</span>(<span class="at">expand =</span> <span class="fu">expansion</span>(<span class="at">mult =</span> <span class="fu">c</span>(<span class="fl">0.002</span>, <span class="dv">0</span>))) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb6-14"><a href="#cb6-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">scale_y_continuous</span>(<span class="at">expand =</span> <span class="fu">expansion</span>(<span class="at">mult =</span> <span class="fu">c</span>(<span class="dv">0</span>, <span class="fl">0.002</span>))) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb6-15"><a href="#cb6-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">labs</span>(</span>
<span id="cb6-16"><a href="#cb6-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">title =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Poverty Rate by Age and Race&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb6-17"><a href="#cb6-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">subtitle =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Whites experience much lower poverty rates than non-Whites at all ages. </span><span class="sc">\n</span><span class="st">Poverty drops when people enter working age, increases around 50, and drops again at retirement.&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb6-18"><a href="#cb6-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">caption =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Source: IPUMS&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb6-19"><a href="#cb6-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">x =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Age&quot;</span>, </span>
<span id="cb6-20"><a href="#cb6-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">y =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Percentage of population in poverty&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb6-21"><a href="#cb6-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">fill =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Race&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb6-22"><a href="#cb6-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  ) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb6-23"><a href="#cb6-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">theme_minimal</span>()</span>
<span id="cb6-24"><a href="#cb6-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb6-25"><a href="#cb6-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>line_by_age</span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
<div class="cell-output-display">
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," class="img-fluid" width="672"></p>
</div>
</div>
<p>Measuring poverty rate in 2018 by age and race it is evident that whites have a significantly lower incidence of poverty than non-whites. The disparity in poverty rates between whites and non-whites is most significant at younger ages, and falls as individuals enter the workforce. Interestingly, we can see that non-whites incidence of poverty increases again around age 45 and that this gap in poverty rates widen as they age. Poverty rates decline briefly after retirement, which can likely be attributed to people getting access to their social security benefits and government provided healthcare, but they rise again as people enter their 70âs and 80âs.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb7"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb7-1"><a href="#cb7-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>states <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> tigris<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">states</span>(<span class="at">cb =</span> <span class="cn">TRUE</span>, <span class="at">year =</span> <span class="dv">2018</span>) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb7-2"><a href="#cb7-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">filter</span>(<span class="sc">!</span>STATEFP <span class="sc">%in%</span> <span class="fu">c</span>(<span class="st">&quot;60&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;69&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;72&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;78&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;66&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;15&quot;</span>, <span class="st">&quot;02&quot;</span>))</span>
<span id="cb7-3"><a href="#cb7-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb7-4"><a href="#cb7-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Group by state and calculate the poverty rate</span></span>
<span id="cb7-5"><a href="#cb7-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cps_svy_map <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">as_survey_design</span>(cps_svy, <span class="at">weights =</span> asecwt) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb7-6"><a href="#cb7-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">filter</span>(year <span class="sc">==</span> <span class="dv">2018</span>, <span class="sc">!</span><span class="fu">is.na</span>(offpov)) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb7-7"><a href="#cb7-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">group_by</span>(statefip) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb7-8"><a href="#cb7-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  srvyr<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">summarize</span>(<span class="at">pov_rate =</span> <span class="fu">survey_mean</span>(offpov)) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb7-9"><a href="#cb7-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">rename</span>(<span class="at">STATEFP =</span> statefip)</span>
<span id="cb7-10"><a href="#cb7-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb7-11"><a href="#cb7-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cps_svy_map<span class="sc">$</span>STATEFP <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">as.character</span>(cps_svy_map<span class="sc">$</span>STATEFP)</span>
<span id="cb7-12"><a href="#cb7-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cps_svy_map<span class="sc">$</span>STATEFP <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">str_pad</span>(cps_svy_map<span class="sc">$</span>STATEFP, <span class="dv">2</span>, <span class="fu">c</span>(<span class="st">&quot;left&quot;</span>), <span class="st">&quot;0&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb7-13"><a href="#cb7-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  </span>
<span id="cb7-14"><a href="#cb7-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>joined_data <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">left_join</span>(states, cps_svy_map, <span class="at">by =</span> <span class="st">&quot;STATEFP&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb7-15"><a href="#cb7-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb7-16"><a href="#cb7-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>map <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> cps_svy_map <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb7-17"><a href="#cb7-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">ggplot</span>() <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb7-18"><a href="#cb7-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">geom_sf</span>(joined_data, <span class="at">mapping =</span> <span class="fu">aes</span>(<span class="at">fill =</span> <span class="fu">as.numeric</span>(pov_rate))) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb7-19"><a href="#cb7-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">scale_fill_gradient</span>(<span class="at">name =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Poverty Rate&quot;</span>, <span class="at">low =</span> <span class="st">&quot;lightblue&quot;</span>, <span class="at">high =</span> <span class="st">&quot;darkblue&quot;</span>) <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb7-20"><a href="#cb7-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">theme_void</span>() <span class="sc">+</span></span>
<span id="cb7-21"><a href="#cb7-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">labs</span>(</span>
<span id="cb7-22"><a href="#cb7-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">title =</span> <span class="st">&quot;Poverty Rate in the Contiguous U.S. in 2018&quot;</span>,</span>
<span id="cb7-23"><a href="#cb7-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>    <span class="at">subtitle=</span> <span class="st">&quot;State-level poverty rates range from 6.6% in New Hampshire to 21% in Louisiana.&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb7-24"><a href="#cb7-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  )</span>
<span id="cb7-25"><a href="#cb7-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb7-26"><a href="#cb7-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>map</span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
<div class="cell-output-display">
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," class="img-fluid" width="672"></p>
</div>
</div>
<p>Looking at the map of contiguous U.S. we can observe there is a wide variation of poverty rates by state. There appears to be a a greater concentration of poverty in southern states such as Louisiana, Arizona, and Mississippi. Meanwhile the lowest incidence of poverty can be seen in the Northeast, along with Colorado and Utah. This map demonstrates that although there are clearly states with a greater concentration of poverty, state geography is likely not the greatest predictor to determine whether an individual will be in poverty.</p>
</section>
<section id="modeling" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="modeling">Modeling</h2>
<p>First, we make a basic decision tree to understand which variables were the most useful in predicting poverty in our data frame. We excluded from our model the other measure of poverty (<code>poverty</code>), as well as household income, from the model, since both of those are directly predictive of poverty, and are thus not useful to us.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb8"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb8-1"><a href="#cb8-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Creating data frame for the analysis</span></span>
<span id="cb8-2"><a href="#cb8-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">as_survey_design</span>(cps_svy, <span class="at">weights =</span> asecwt) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-3"><a href="#cb8-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">select</span>(<span class="sc">-</span>poverty, <span class="sc">-</span>hhincome)</span>
<span id="cb8-4"><a href="#cb8-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">as.data.frame</span>(weighted_cps)</span>
<span id="cb8-5"><a href="#cb8-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-6"><a href="#cb8-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_models <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> weighted_cps <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-7"><a href="#cb8-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">drop_na</span>(offpov) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-8"><a href="#cb8-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">mutate</span>(<span class="at">offpov =</span> <span class="fu">as.factor</span>(offpov)) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> </span>
<span id="cb8-9"><a href="#cb8-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">select</span>(<span class="sc">-</span>year) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-10"><a href="#cb8-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">mutate_at</span>(<span class="fu">vars</span>(immigrant,</span>
<span id="cb8-11"><a href="#cb8-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 pubhous,</span>
<span id="cb8-12"><a href="#cb8-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 foodstmp,</span>
<span id="cb8-13"><a href="#cb8-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 sex,</span>
<span id="cb8-14"><a href="#cb8-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 vetstat,</span>
<span id="cb8-15"><a href="#cb8-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 labforce,</span>
<span id="cb8-16"><a href="#cb8-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 diffany,</span>
<span id="cb8-17"><a href="#cb8-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 himcarely,</span>
<span id="cb8-18"><a href="#cb8-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 phinsur,</span>
<span id="cb8-19"><a href="#cb8-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 anycovnw,</span>
<span id="cb8-20"><a href="#cb8-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 kidcneed,</span>
<span id="cb8-21"><a href="#cb8-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                 workly), </span>
<span id="cb8-22"><a href="#cb8-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>            <span class="fu">list</span>(<span class="sc">~</span> <span class="fu">as.factor</span>(.))</span>
<span id="cb8-23"><a href="#cb8-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  )</span>
<span id="cb8-24"><a href="#cb8-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-25"><a href="#cb8-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">set.seed</span>(<span class="dv">20211101</span>)</span>
<span id="cb8-26"><a href="#cb8-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-27"><a href="#cb8-27" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Creating a split object:</span></span>
<span id="cb8-28"><a href="#cb8-28" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_split <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">initial_split</span>(<span class="at">data =</span> weighted_cps_models, <span class="at">prop =</span> <span class="fl">0.8</span>)</span>
<span id="cb8-29"><a href="#cb8-29" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-30"><a href="#cb8-30" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Creating the training and testing data:</span></span>
<span id="cb8-31"><a href="#cb8-31" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">training</span>(<span class="at">x =</span> weighted_cps_split) </span>
<span id="cb8-32"><a href="#cb8-32" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">testing</span>(<span class="at">x =</span> weighted_cps_split)</span>
<span id="cb8-33"><a href="#cb8-33" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-34"><a href="#cb8-34" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Creating a recipe:</span></span>
<span id="cb8-35"><a href="#cb8-35" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cart_rec <span class="ot">&lt;-</span></span>
<span id="cb8-36"><a href="#cb8-36" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">recipe</span>(<span class="at">formula =</span> offpov <span class="sc">~</span> ., <span class="at">data =</span> weighted_cps_train)</span>
<span id="cb8-37"><a href="#cb8-37" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-38"><a href="#cb8-38" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Creating a cart model object:</span></span>
<span id="cb8-39"><a href="#cb8-39" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cart_mod <span class="ot">&lt;-</span></span>
<span id="cb8-40"><a href="#cb8-40" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">decision_tree</span>() <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-41"><a href="#cb8-41" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">set_engine</span>(<span class="at">engine =</span> <span class="st">&quot;rpart&quot;</span>) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-42"><a href="#cb8-42" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">set_mode</span>(<span class="at">mode =</span> <span class="st">&quot;classification&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb8-43"><a href="#cb8-43" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cart_wf <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">workflow</span>() <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-44"><a href="#cb8-44" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">add_recipe</span>(cart_rec) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-45"><a href="#cb8-45" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">add_model</span>(cart_mod)</span>
<span id="cb8-46"><a href="#cb8-46" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-47"><a href="#cb8-47" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Fitting the model:</span></span>
<span id="cb8-48"><a href="#cb8-48" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>cart_fit <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> cart_wf <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb8-49"><a href="#cb8-49" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">fit</span>(<span class="at">data =</span> weighted_cps_train)</span>
<span id="cb8-50"><a href="#cb8-50" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb8-51"><a href="#cb8-51" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Creating a tree:</span></span>
<span id="cb8-52"><a href="#cb8-52" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rpart.plot<span class="sc">::</span><span class="fu">rpart.plot</span>(<span class="at">x =</span> cart_fit<span class="sc">$</span>fit<span class="sc">$</span>fit<span class="sc">$</span>fit, <span class="at">roundint=</span><span class="cn">FALSE</span>)</span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
<div class="cell-output-display">
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," class="img-fluid" width="672"></p>
</div>
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb9"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb9-1"><a href="#cb9-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Predicting the predicted class and the predicted probability of each class:</span></span>
<span id="cb9-2"><a href="#cb9-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>predictions <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">bind_cols</span>(</span>
<span id="cb9-3"><a href="#cb9-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  weighted_cps_test,</span>
<span id="cb9-4"><a href="#cb9-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">predict</span>(<span class="at">object =</span> cart_fit, <span class="at">new_data =</span> weighted_cps_test),</span>
<span id="cb9-5"><a href="#cb9-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">predict</span>(<span class="at">object =</span> cart_fit, <span class="at">new_data =</span> weighted_cps_test, <span class="at">type =</span> <span class="st">&quot;prob&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb9-6"><a href="#cb9-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>)</span>
<span id="cb9-7"><a href="#cb9-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">select</span>(predictions, offpov, <span class="fu">starts_with</span>(<span class="st">&quot;.pred&quot;</span>))</span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
<p>As we can see in this decision tree, important variables in predicting whether someone was in poverty or not are: whether they received food stamps (<code>foodstmp</code>, currently known as SNAP), and if so, how much (<code>stampval</code>); total family medical out of pocket payments (<code>moop</code>); whether the respondent worked last year (<code>workly</code>); their Social Security income (<code>incss</code>); and family size (<code>famsize</code>). Those who received SNAP benefits and had high out of pocket medical expenditures were more likely to end up in poverty.</p>
<p>The next step is to construct a random forest:</p>
<p>First we create the data frame we will use for our modeling, filtering out NA values from offpov, and turning variables into factors. We then set the seed and split the data into a test set and a training set. Next we created a recipe for the random forest model, turning categorical variables into dummy variables. Lastly, we created a random forest model setting the engine to ranger and mode to classification. After creating a workflow, we create a grid for parameters and then attempt to execute it. At this point, our model fails to run any further. Unfortunately, we were unable to calculate the ROC_AUC or accuracy of our model for this reason. If successful, the random forest model would have allowed us to isolate the variables of greatest importance for predicting poverty at an individual level.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb10"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb10-1"><a href="#cb10-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Creating dataframe for random forest model</span></span>
<span id="cb10-2"><a href="#cb10-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rf_model_cps_2018 <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> weighted_cps_2018 <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb10-3"><a href="#cb10-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">filter</span>(<span class="sc">!</span><span class="fu">is.na</span>(offpov)) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb10-4"><a href="#cb10-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> <span class="fu">mutate</span>(<span class="at">offpov =</span> <span class="fu">as.factor</span>(offpov)) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> <span class="co"># Here we make our y variable a factor variable</span></span>
<span id="cb10-5"><a href="#cb10-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> <span class="fu">select</span> (<span class="sc">-</span> year  , <span class="sc">-</span> county , <span class="sc">-</span>poverty , <span class="sc">-</span>hhincome , <span class="sc">-</span>asecwt , <span class="sc">-</span>stampval , yrimmig , moop) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> <span class="co"># We remove variables we don&#39;t want to include as predictors</span></span>
<span id="cb10-6"><a href="#cb10-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>   <span class="fu">mutate_at</span>(<span class="fu">vars</span>(metro, statefip, pubhous, vetstat, empstat, labforce, occ, ind, classwkr, uhrsworkt, educ, diffany, occly, indly, classwly, workly, incint, migrate1, himcarely, kidcneed, union), <span class="fu">list</span>(<span class="sc">~</span> <span class="fu">as.factor</span>(.))) </span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb11"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb11-1"><a href="#cb11-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Set seed so model is consistent</span></span>
<span id="cb11-2"><a href="#cb11-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">set.seed</span>(<span class="dv">12122022</span>)</span>
<span id="cb11-3"><a href="#cb11-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Split data frame into training and testing data</span></span>
<span id="cb11-4"><a href="#cb11-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>split <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">initial_split</span>(rf_model_cps_2018)</span>
<span id="cb11-5"><a href="#cb11-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb11-6"><a href="#cb11-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rf_cps_2018_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">remove_val_labels</span>(<span class="fu">training</span>(split))</span>
<span id="cb11-7"><a href="#cb11-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rf__cps_2018_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">remove_val_labels</span>(<span class="fu">testing</span>(split))</span>
<span id="cb11-8"><a href="#cb11-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb11-9"><a href="#cb11-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Set up 5 folds</span></span>
<span id="cb11-10"><a href="#cb11-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>folds <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">vfold_cv</span>(<span class="at">data =</span> rf_cps_2018_train, <span class="at">v =</span> <span class="dv">5</span>)</span>
<span id="cb11-11"><a href="#cb11-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb11-12"><a href="#cb11-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Create a recipe for random forest model </span></span>
<span id="cb11-13"><a href="#cb11-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb11-14"><a href="#cb11-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rf_rec <span class="ot">&lt;-</span></span>
<span id="cb11-15"><a href="#cb11-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">recipe</span>(offpov <span class="sc">~</span> ., <span class="at">data =</span> rf_cps_2018_train) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb11-16"><a href="#cb11-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_dummy</span>(metro, statefip, pubhous, vetstat, empstat, labforce, occ, ind, classwkr, uhrsworkt, educ, diffany, occly, indly, classwly, workly, incint, migrate1, himcarely, kidcneed, union) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> <span class="co">#Turn select categorical variables into dummies</span></span>
<span id="cb11-17"><a href="#cb11-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_center</span>(<span class="fu">all_numeric_predictors</span>()) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> <span class="co"># this centers predictors</span></span>
<span id="cb11-18"><a href="#cb11-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_scale</span>(<span class="fu">all_numeric_predictors</span>()) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> <span class="co"># this scales predictors</span></span>
<span id="cb11-19"><a href="#cb11-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_nzv</span>(<span class="fu">all_numeric_predictors</span>()) <span class="co"># this drops near zero variance predictors</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb12"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb12-1"><a href="#cb12-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Making a random forest model </span></span>
<span id="cb12-2"><a href="#cb12-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rf_model <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">rand_forest</span>(<span class="at">mtry =</span> <span class="dv">10</span>, <span class="at">min_n =</span> <span class="fu">tune</span>(), <span class="at">trees =</span> <span class="dv">100</span>) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-3"><a href="#cb12-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">set_engine</span>(<span class="st">&quot;ranger&quot;</span>, <span class="at">importance =</span> <span class="st">&quot;impurity&quot;</span>) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-4"><a href="#cb12-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">set_mode</span>(<span class="st">&quot;classification&quot;</span>)</span>

<span id="cb12-6"><a href="#cb12-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Create a workflow</span></span>
<span id="cb12-7"><a href="#cb12-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rf_workflow <span class="ot">&lt;-</span></span>
<span id="cb12-8"><a href="#cb12-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">workflow</span>() <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-9"><a href="#cb12-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">add_model</span>(rf_model) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-10"><a href="#cb12-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">add_recipe</span>(rf_rec)</span>
<span id="cb12-11"><a href="#cb12-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb12-12"><a href="#cb12-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Create a grid of the parameters</span></span>
<span id="cb12-13"><a href="#cb12-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>rf_grid <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">grid_regular</span>(</span>
<span id="cb12-14"><a href="#cb12-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">min_n</span>(<span class="at">range =</span> <span class="fu">c</span>(<span class="dv">2</span>, <span class="dv">8</span>)),</span>
<span id="cb12-15"><a href="#cb12-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="at">levels =</span> <span class="dv">4</span>)</span>
<span id="cb12-16"><a href="#cb12-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb12-17"><a href="#cb12-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Execute hyperparameter tuning using the grid and the cross_validation folds - here is where the code takes too long to run</span></span>
<span id="cb12-18"><a href="#cb12-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#rf_cv &lt;- tune_grid(rf_workflow,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-19"><a href="#cb12-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                   <span class="co">#resamples = folds,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-20"><a href="#cb12-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                   <span class="co">#grid = rf_grid,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-21"><a href="#cb12-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                   <span class="co">#metrics = metric_set(roc_auc))</span></span>
<span id="cb12-22"><a href="#cb12-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb12-23"><a href="#cb12-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Calculate ROC_AUC and accuracy</span></span>
<span id="cb12-24"><a href="#cb12-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#collect_metrics(rf_cv, summarize = TRUE) %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-25"><a href="#cb12-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#filter(.metric == &quot;roc_auc&quot;)</span></span>
<span id="cb12-26"><a href="#cb12-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb12-27"><a href="#cb12-27" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Select the best model based on roc_auc</span></span>
<span id="cb12-28"><a href="#cb12-28" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#rf_best_model &lt;- rf_cv %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-29"><a href="#cb12-29" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#select_best(metric = &quot;roc_auc&quot;)</span></span>
<span id="cb12-30"><a href="#cb12-30" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb12-31"><a href="#cb12-31" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Finalize model</span></span>
<span id="cb12-32"><a href="#cb12-32" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#rf_final_model &lt;- finalize_model(rf_model, rf_best_model)</span></span>
<span id="cb12-33"><a href="#cb12-33" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Evaluate variable importance</span></span>
<span id="cb12-34"><a href="#cb12-34" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#rf_last_fit %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-35"><a href="#cb12-35" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#extract_fit_parsnip() %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb12-36"><a href="#cb12-36" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#vip::vip(num_features = 15)</span></span>
<span id="cb12-37"><a href="#cb12-37" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#rf_predictions &lt;- bind_cols(rf__cps_2018_test,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-38"><a href="#cb12-38" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                            <span class="co">#predict(object = rf_last_fit, new_data = rf__cps_2018_test),</span></span>
<span id="cb12-39"><a href="#cb12-39" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>                            <span class="co">#predict(object = rf_last_fit, new_data = rf__cps_2018_test, type = &quot;prob&quot;))</span></span>
<span id="cb12-40"><a href="#cb12-40" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb12-41"><a href="#cb12-41" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># To evaluate the model calculate...</span></span>
<span id="cb12-42"><a href="#cb12-42" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Confusion matrix</span></span>
<span id="cb12-43"><a href="#cb12-43" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#conf_mat(data = rf_predictions,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-44"><a href="#cb12-44" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>         <span class="co">#truth = offpov,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-45"><a href="#cb12-45" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>         <span class="co">#estimate = .pred_class)</span></span>
<span id="cb12-46"><a href="#cb12-46" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Accuracy</span></span>
<span id="cb12-47"><a href="#cb12-47" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#accuracy(data = rf_predictions,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-48"><a href="#cb12-48" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>          <span class="co">#truth = offpov,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-49"><a href="#cb12-49" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>          <span class="co">#estimate = .pred_class)</span></span>
<span id="cb12-50"><a href="#cb12-50" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># ROC_AUC metric</span></span>
<span id="cb12-51"><a href="#cb12-51" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#roc_auc(data = rf_predictions,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-52"><a href="#cb12-52" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>     <span class="co">#truth = employed,</span></span>
<span id="cb12-53"><a href="#cb12-53" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>     <span class="co">#estimate = .pred_0)</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
<p>The next attempted model was k nearest neighbors:</p>
<p>In the KNN model, we attempted to predict the value of <code>offpov</code> with the predictive variables in the weighted CPS data frame. We decided to tune the number of neighbors based on the best model that would have resulted from the fit into the folds we created. Unfortunately, we were unable to fit the model because of an error we kept incurring into. The error message appeared whenever we tried to fit the model into the folds we created, and didnât disappear no matter how we tweaked the data or the steps in the modelâs recipe.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb13"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb13-1"><a href="#cb13-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Creating folds:</span></span>
<span id="cb13-2"><a href="#cb13-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#folds &lt;- vfold_cv(data = weighted_cps_train, v = 5)</span></span>

<span id="cb13-4"><a href="#cb13-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#weighted_cps_rec &lt;- </span></span>
<span id="cb13-5"><a href="#cb13-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#recipe(formula = offpov ~ ., data = weighted_cps_train) %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb13-6"><a href="#cb13-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#step_dummy(immigrant, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-7"><a href="#cb13-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#pubhous, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-8"><a href="#cb13-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#foodstmp, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-9"><a href="#cb13-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#sex, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-10"><a href="#cb13-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#etstat, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-11"><a href="#cb13-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#labforce, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-12"><a href="#cb13-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#diffany, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-13"><a href="#cb13-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#himcaidly, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-14"><a href="#cb13-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#himcarely, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-15"><a href="#cb13-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#phinsur, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-16"><a href="#cb13-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#anycovnw, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-17"><a href="#cb13-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#kidcneed, </span></span>
<span id="cb13-18"><a href="#cb13-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>             <span class="co">#workly)</span></span>
<span id="cb13-19"><a href="#cb13-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#step_center(all_numeric_predictors()) %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb13-20"><a href="#cb13-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#step_scale(all_numeric_predictors()) %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb13-21"><a href="#cb13-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#step_nzv(all_numeric_predictors()) %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb13-22"><a href="#cb13-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#step_impute_knn(all_predictors()) %&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb13-23"><a href="#cb13-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#step_other()</span></span>
<span id="cb13-24"><a href="#cb13-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  </span>
<span id="cb13-25"><a href="#cb13-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Creating a KNN model with hyper parameter tuning:</span></span>
<span id="cb13-26"><a href="#cb13-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Creating a KNN model specification:</span></span>
<span id="cb13-27"><a href="#cb13-27" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#weighted_cps_knn_mod &lt;-</span></span>

<span id="cb13-30"><a href="#cb13-30" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#set_mode(mode = &quot;classification&quot;)</span></span>
<span id="cb13-31"><a href="#cb13-31" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Creating a workflow:</span></span>
<span id="cb13-32"><a href="#cb13-32" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#weighted_cps_knn_workflow &lt;-</span></span>

<span id="cb13-35"><a href="#cb13-35" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#add_recipe(recipe = weighted_cps_rec)</span></span>
<span id="cb13-36"><a href="#cb13-36" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Creating a tuning grid:</span></span>
<span id="cb13-37"><a href="#cb13-37" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#weighted_cps_knn_grid &lt;- grid_regular(neighbors(range = c(1, 15)), levels = 2)</span></span>
<span id="cb13-38"><a href="#cb13-38" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co"># Estimating models with re-sampling for each row in the tuning grid:</span></span>
<span id="cb13-39"><a href="#cb13-39" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#weighted_cps_knn_res &lt;- weighted_cps_knn_workflow %&gt;% </span></span>
<span id="cb13-40"><a href="#cb13-40" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#tune_grid(resamples = folds,</span></span>
<span id="cb13-41"><a href="#cb13-41" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>            <span class="co">#grid = weighted_cps_knn_grid,</span></span>
<span id="cb13-42"><a href="#cb13-42" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>            <span class="co">#control = control_grid(save_pred = TRUE),</span></span>
<span id="cb13-43"><a href="#cb13-43" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>            <span class="co">#metrics = metric_set(accuracy))</span></span></code><button title="Copy to Clipboard" class="code-copy-button"><i class="bi"></i></button></pre></div>
</div>
<p>Finally, our last intended model was a LASSO model:</p>
<p>The process we went through for this model was similar as for the others. We cleaned the data for this specific model, which included turning all the NAs into 0s. We then went through the process of splitting the data, creating a recipe, making a model, and a workflow, and attempting to apply the new model to our data. Alas, we ran into an issue here as well. This time, however, we managed to get the RMSE associated with each fold. No amount of fiddling with the recipe or cleaning of the data resulted in a successful model.</p>
<div class="cell">
<div class="sourceCode cell-code" id="cb14"><pre class="sourceCode r code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode r"><span id="cb14-1"><a href="#cb14-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Preparing the data</span></span>
<span id="cb14-2"><a href="#cb14-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb14-3"><a href="#cb14-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Deleting year</span></span>
<span id="cb14-4"><a href="#cb14-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_2018_lasso <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> weighted_cps_2018 <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb14-5"><a href="#cb14-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">select</span>(<span class="sc">-</span>year, <span class="sc">-</span>asecwt)</span>
<span id="cb14-6"><a href="#cb14-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb14-7"><a href="#cb14-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Turning NAs into 0s</span></span>
<span id="cb14-8"><a href="#cb14-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_2018_lasso[<span class="fu">is.na</span>(weighted_cps_2018_lasso)] <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="dv">0</span></span>
<span id="cb14-9"><a href="#cb14-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb14-10"><a href="#cb14-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">set.seed</span>(<span class="dv">12122022</span>)</span>
<span id="cb14-11"><a href="#cb14-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>split <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">initial_split</span>(weighted_cps_2018_lasso)</span>
<span id="cb14-12"><a href="#cb14-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb14-13"><a href="#cb14-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_2018_train <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">training</span>(split)</span>
<span id="cb14-14"><a href="#cb14-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_2018_test <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">testing</span>(split)</span>
<span id="cb14-15"><a href="#cb14-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb14-16"><a href="#cb14-16" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Set up resampling</span></span>
<span id="cb14-17"><a href="#cb14-17" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>folds1 <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">vfold_cv</span>(weighted_cps_2018_train, <span class="at">v =</span> <span class="dv">5</span>)</span>
<span id="cb14-18"><a href="#cb14-18" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb14-19"><a href="#cb14-19" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Create a tuning grid for lasso regularization</span></span>
<span id="cb14-20"><a href="#cb14-20" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>lasso_grid <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">grid_regular</span>(<span class="fu">penalty</span>(), <span class="at">levels =</span> <span class="dv">10</span>)</span>
<span id="cb14-21"><a href="#cb14-21" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb14-22"><a href="#cb14-22" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="co">#Creating a recipe</span></span>
<span id="cb14-23"><a href="#cb14-23" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>weighted_cps_2018_rec <span class="ot">&lt;-</span> <span class="fu">recipe</span>(offpov <span class="sc">~</span> ., <span class="at">data =</span> weighted_cps_2018_train) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span></span>
<span id="cb14-24"><a href="#cb14-24" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_dummy</span>(<span class="fu">all_nominal</span>(), <span class="sc">-</span><span class="fu">all_outcomes</span>()) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> </span>
<span id="cb14-25"><a href="#cb14-25" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_center</span>(<span class="fu">all_predictors</span>()) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> <span class="co"># center predictors</span></span>
<span id="cb14-26"><a href="#cb14-26" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_scale</span>(<span class="fu">all_predictors</span>()) <span class="sc">%&gt;%</span> <span class="co"># scale predictors</span></span>
<span id="cb14-27"><a href="#cb14-27" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="fu">step_nzv</span>(<span class="fu">all_predictors</span>()) <span class="co"># drop near zero variance for all predictors</span></span>
<span id="cb14-28"><a href="#cb14-28" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <span class="co">#step_other(all_predictors())  # collapse low-frequency categories</span></span>
<span id="cb14-29"><a href="#cb14-29" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> </span>
<span id="cb14-30"><a href="#cb14-30" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
